     434    [MS-XCEP] — v20090223
     501    services permits traditional protocol boundaries for X.509 enrollment to be lifted. [MS-XCEP] begins
     503    (request/response) and subsequent closure of the secure tunnel. The [MS-XCEP] specification does
     512    [MS-XCEP] — v20090223
     559    [MS-XCEP] — v20090223
     572    to provide clients with policy guidance for the X.509 certificate life cycle. [MS-XCEP] is not required
